<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 27 日星期六 13:17:54 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Ukrainian Military Starts Training in Germany to Operate US Abrams Tanks - Reports]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110636622" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/19173/69/191736959_0:0:1024:683_1440x900_80_0_1_27ef644ec5c7a0b893f31505c6fc33e4.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="191736958" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/ukrainian-military-starts-training-in-germany-to-operate-us-abrams-tanks---reports-1110636622.html?share-img=191736958"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片：Joseph A. Lambach，美国海军陆战队/维基百科</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">M1A1 艾布拉姆斯坦克</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="M1A1 Abrams tank - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="M1A1艾布拉姆斯坦克" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/19173/69/191736959_0:54:1025:630_1920x0_80_0_0_83aef01983c5887d8cc692af7ee7d12c.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/19173/69/191736959_0:54:1025:630_640x0_80_0_0_b89f1c0e14ae1d1dc6b79487fbe0bb1a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/19173/69/191736959_0:54:1025:630_1280x0_80_0_0_e8da1d93ed6d224b705515fb5ed0d3cd.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/19173/69/191736959_0:54:1025:630_1920x0_80_0_0_83aef01983c5887d8cc692af7ee7d12c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片：Joseph A. Lambach，美国海军陆战队/维基百科</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：美国一家报纸周六援引五角大楼发言人的话说，约有 400 名驻扎在德国的乌克兰士兵已经开始接受操作美国制造的 M1 艾布拉姆斯坦克的训练。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据援引发言人加伦·加恩的话说，周五，大约 200 名乌克兰士兵开始在格拉芬沃尔和霍恩费尔斯的训练场进行联合武装训练，另有 200 人开始接受坦克加油和维修方面的训练。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自2022年2月俄罗斯在乌克兰开始军事行动以来，西方国家一直在向基辅提供军事援助。援助从火炮弹药和训练发展到包括坦克在内的重型武器。几个月来， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/why-does-ukraine-want-f-16s-1110518595.html" target="_blank">乌克兰一直在敦促捐助者提供战斗机</a>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">直到上周，白宫才同意欧洲盟友向乌克兰派遣他们的美制 F16 喷气式飞机——基辅的首选战斗机。德国表示不会派遣战斗机，但会继续以其他方式支持乌克兰。克里姆林宫一再警告不要向基辅运送西方武器。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 12:45:48 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/ukrainian-military-starts-training-in-germany-to-operate-us-abrams-tanks---reports-1110636622.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/ukrainian-military-starts-training-in-germany-to-operate-us-abrams-tanks---reports-1110636622.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>乌克兰危机</category><category>艾布拉姆斯坦克</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Beijing, Seoul Agree on Semiconductor Industry Chains Amid China-US Chip Race]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110627904" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102377/61/1023776126_0:0:1020:612_1440x900_80_0_1_bc0b35000b52fc6f3cede196ddfe36e7.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1023776125" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/beijing-seoul-agree-on-semiconductor-industry-chains-amid-china-us-chip-race-1110627904.html?share-img=1023776125"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Photo : Institute/Design Museum</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2023 年 5 月 26 日，中国商务部部长王文涛宣布北京与首尔就半导体产业达成共识</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="On May 26, 2023, Chinese Commerce Minister Wang Wentao announced a consensus between Beijing and Seoul on semiconductor industry - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="2023年5月26日，中国商务部部长王文涛宣布北京与首尔就半导体产业达成共识" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102377/61/1023776126_0:19:1020:593_1920x0_80_0_0_0c11b973748622152ed8ad03e0255579.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102377/61/1023776126_0:19:1020:593_640x0_80_0_0_fcaeb6b16903e0657f13ca05b111925c.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102377/61/1023776126_0:19:1020:593_1280x0_80_0_0_8d95a035e5f18ea2b2bb9a46e7aeccdd.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102377/61/1023776126_0:19:1020:593_1920x0_80_0_0_0c11b973748622152ed8ad03e0255579.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片：研究所/设计博物馆</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Oleg Burunov - Sputnik International" title="奥列格布鲁诺夫" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/09/0b/1080424846_0:0:2048:2048_100x100_80_0_0_3d7b461f8a98586fa3fe739930816aea.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">奥列格布鲁诺夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_burunov_oleg/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:o.burunov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">韩国向中国和美国提供半导体，这两个国家在全球竞争中继续争夺生产最好芯片的角力。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">中国商务部长王文涛宣布了北京和首尔就<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220712/intel-urges-us-congress-to-pass-chips-act-to-fund-semiconductors-industry-amid-shortage-1097245461.html" target="_blank">半导体产业</a>达成的共识。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>王告诉记者，这个问题是他在周五结束的底特律亚太经合组织会议期间与韩国外长安德根会谈的首要议程。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110627904" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/beijing-seoul-agree-on-semiconductor-industry-chains-amid-china-us-chip-race-1110627904.html?share-block=1110627906" data-title="Wang told reporters that the issue topped the agenda of his talks with his South Korean counterpart Ahn Duk-geun on the sidelines of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) conference in Detroit, which wrapped up on Friday."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">中国商务部部长补充说，在谈判期间，双方就维护<strong>半导体产业供应链的稳定</strong>以及促进双边、区域和多边领域的合作交换了意见。他表示，中国愿与韩国深化经贸关系和投资合作。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>与此同时，一家美国媒体援引一位不愿透露姓名的消息人士的话称，韩国方面表示有信心“所有行业的工作级别官员之间都需要[双边]沟通”，而不仅仅是半导体。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110627904" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/beijing-seoul-agree-on-semiconductor-industry-chains-amid-china-us-chip-race-1110627904.html?share-block=1110627908" data-title="A US media outlet has meanwhile cited an unnamed source as saying that the South Korean side had expressed confidence that “[bilateral] communication is needed between working-level officials over all industries,&amp;quot; not just for semiconductors."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> APEC 会议召开之际，首尔正处于美国和中国争夺全球芯片行业主导权的十字路口，预计到 2030 年全球芯片行业的收入将增长到<strong>1.4 万亿美元</strong>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">由于所谓的国家安全风险，华盛顿呼吁限制北京获取先进芯片，韩国仍然是中国和美国的半导体供应商。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">美中芯片大赛</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据白宫称，美国和中国目前在全球芯片生产中的份额分别为<strong>10%</strong>和<strong>15%</strong> 。华盛顿正努力通过进一步限制和扩大对国内芯片行业的投资来赢得与北京的竞争。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2022 年 10 月，拜登政府对北京的芯片制造业实施了迄今为止最广泛的限制，要求那些使用美国工具或软件向中国出口芯片的公司获得许可，无论它们是在世界何处制造的。这些措施还阻止美国公民和绿卡持有人为某些中国芯片公司工作。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在这些限制之前，乔·拜登总统签署了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220825/biden-signs-executive-order-implementing-chips-and-science-act-of-2022-1099999690.htm" target="_blank">两党 CHIPS 和科学法案</a>，其中包括为生产半导体的美国公司提供超过<strong>520 亿美元的资金</strong>，以及数十亿美元的税收抵免以鼓励对该行业的投资。目的是防止美国投资者直接或间接为中国半导体生产的发展做出贡献。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2"> APEC底特律论坛</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">APEC 会议于 5 月 14 日至 26 日在底特律举行，来自该组织<strong>21 个成员国的贸易部长、高级官员和工作级专家齐聚一堂。</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> APEC 秘书处执行主任 Rebecca Sta Maria 告诉记者，“随着亚太地区从 COVID-19 大流行中走出来，我们 [底特律论坛] 的议程将为成员提供一个参与的机会，并让他们零参与我们可以确保国际跨境贸易顺畅流动，以及贸易如何帮助我们应对该地区从气候变化到经济不平等的最紧迫挑战。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110627904" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/beijing-seoul-agree-on-semiconductor-industry-chains-amid-china-us-chip-race-1110627904.html?share-block=1110635193" data-title="Rebecca Sta Maria, Executive Director of the APEC Secretariat, told reporters that “as the Asia-Pacific region emerges from the COVID-19 pandemic, our agenda [of the Detroit forum] will provide an opportunity for members to engage and zero in on how we can ensure international cross-border trade flows smoothly, and how trade can help us address the region’s most pressing challenges from climate change to economic inequality.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在会议期间，亚太经合组织部长们特别讨论了相互合作如何促进可持续和包容性贸易的实际步骤。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> APEC 成立于<strong>1989 年</strong>，旨在利用亚太地区日益相互依存的优势，包括澳大利亚、文莱、中国、香港、印度尼西亚、日本、韩国、马来西亚、新西兰、巴布亚新几内亚、菲律宾、俄罗斯、新加坡、泰国、越南，还有美国、加拿大、墨西哥、智利和秘鲁。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 12:41:33 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/beijing-seoul-agree-on-semiconductor-industry-chains-amid-china-us-chip-race-1110627904.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/beijing-seoul-agree-on-semiconductor-industry-chains-amid-china-us-chip-race-1110627904.html<category>经济</category><category>中国</category><category>韩国</category><category>我们</category><category>啐</category><category>半导体</category><category>筹码</category><category>协议</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukraine Loses Over 260 Troops Near Donetsk - MoD]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110636299" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/11/1106425217_0:0:3033:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_21c8befc40e46934162c03f17096e7e8.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1106425200" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/ukraine-loses-over-260-troops-near-donetsk---mod-1110636299.html?share-img=1106425200"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Alexey Maishev</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯军人</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Russian serviceman - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="俄罗斯军人" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/11/1106425217_0:171:3033:1877_1920x0_80_0_0_1d226abb753d134bd916dd96eebf0980.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/11/1106425217_0:171:3033:1877_640x0_80_0_0_4a55c8c1001c16136299f59463398c8c.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/11/1106425217_0:171:3033:1877_1280x0_80_0_0_f4cfcb69b2eee95396c38027c8536cf4.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/11/1106425217_0:171:3033:1877_1920x0_80_0_0_1d226abb753d134bd916dd96eebf0980.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Alexey Maishev</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：俄罗斯国防部在周六的每日更新中说，过去一天，乌克兰在东部城市顿涅茨克附近与俄罗斯军队的战斗中损失了 260 多名军事人员。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “在顿涅茨克方向，超过 260 名乌克兰军人……在过去 24 小时内被作战战术和陆军航空兵、大炮以及与‘南方’武装部队的部队进行的打击所消灭，”俄罗斯军方说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">俄罗斯军队还摧毁了两辆装甲车、一辆 Gvozdika 自行榴弹炮和两辆 122 毫米 D-30 榴弹炮，以及顿涅茨克北部 Avdeevka 市附近的一个弹药库。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">同一时期，俄罗斯防空系统击落了两枚风暴影子巡航导弹、19 枚 HIMARS 远程导弹、两枚 HARM 反辐射导弹和 12 架无人机。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 12:39:31 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/ukraine-loses-over-260-troops-near-donetsk---mod-1110636299.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/ukraine-loses-over-260-troops-near-donetsk---mod-1110636299.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>乌克兰危机</category></item></channel></rss>